entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An AI operating system designed to facilitate the creation and deployment of AI agents. It focuses on providing tools and infrastructure for AI development, including command-line interfaces and APIs for managing agent functionality.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A platform for software development, offering version control, collaboration tools, and code hosting. It is widely used by developers to manage projects, track changes, and contribute to open-source software.

entities.name: @shawmakesmagic
entities.description: The corrected Twitter handle for ElizaOS, previously subject to confusion.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform designed for communities to chat, voice call, and video call. It is popular among gamers and online communities for its server-based chat structure.

entities.name: Farcaster
entities.description: A decentralized social network protocol that enables the creation of social applications. It focuses on user ownership of data and provides a framework for building social experiences.

entities.name: X
entities.description: A social media platform, formerly known as Twitter, used for microblogging, real-time updates, and public conversations. It features short text posts, images, and videos.

entities.name: Substack
entities.description: A popular online platform that allows writers to publish newsletters and build their audience. It supports both free and paid subscriptions, enabling creators to monetize their content.
